@300  = ~CHAPTER FOUR

    After few hours of uninterrupted sail you see a shiny circlet on the horizon. It is the portal! Saemon slows "Gallante" down. Your seasoned captain looks nervous as the ship enters the time gate. "Athkatla" says he steadily... and the familiar harbor appears in view... You do not stop in the port however, but lay your course straight for Brinnlaw.
    
    Aster and Sime have proven trustworthy. The journey is uneventful, and if there were other ships on the same course they must have kept a discreet distance. You make good time, and soon there is a sizable island on the horizon. It might have been considered a pleasant place, but a grim shadow extends the length of it. The asylum, Spellhold, looms from a cliff side.~ [vptheme2]
@301  = ~CHAPTER FOUR

    After few hours of uninterrupted sail you see a shiny circlet on the horizon. It is the portal! Saemon slows "Gallante" down. Your seasoned captain looks nervous as the ship enters the time gate. "Athkatla" says he steadily... and the familiar harbor appears in view... You do not stop in the port however, but lay your course straight for Maztica... or so you thought.
    
    Malficus was following the orders of Bodhi, a powerful vampire, and you were found at the shore of Brynnlaw, betrayed. Like it or not, you are here now, and the only way to get back is to go forward. The island might have been considered a pleasant place, but a grim shadow extends the length of it. The asylum, Spellhold, looms from a cliff side, and both Irenicus and Imoen are here.~ [vptheme2]

